title: Best photos from Can-Am Duel at Daytona
text:
Feb 23, 2017 at 7:48p ET 0Shares 
The Can-Am Duel qualifying races at Daytona International Speedway sets the field for Sunday's 59th annual Daytona 500 (2 p.m. ET on FOX). 
Check out the best photos from Thursday night's qualifying races: USA Today Images Air Titans 
The Air Titans were working overtime, but to no avail as rain throughout the day washed out practice for the Duel qualifying races. USA Today Images 
Kasey Kahne's team rolls the No. 5 Hendrick Motorsports Chevrolet through the pre-race inspection process. USA Today Images Legendary voice 
Legendary broadcaster Ken Squier poses for a selfie with a fan as Dale Earnhardt Jr.'s No. 88 Hendrick Motorsports Chevrolet rolls by before the race. FOXSports.com Tom Jensen Seven-time 
Seven-time NASCAR Cup Series champion Jimmie Johnson (right) talks to XFINITY Series driver Bubba Wallace on pit road before the Duel. USA Today Images Driver introductions 
Rookie Joe Gibbs Racing driver Daniel Suarez (left) and Team Penske's Joey Logano ride around the track during driver introductions. USA Today Images Dale Jr. makes his return 
Daytona 500 outside pole-sitter Dale Earnhardt Jr. hangs out before participating in the Duel race No. 2 at Daytona. USA Today Images Stewart-Haas Racing 
Stewart-Haas Racing teammates Kurt Busch (left) and Danica Patrick chat after being introduced to the fans at Daytona. USA Today Images Daytona 500 pole sitter 
Daytona 500 pole-sitter Chase Elliott is all smiles before the start of Duel race No. 1. USA Today Images Green flag 
Chase Elliott (24) and Brad Keselowski (2) lead the field to green in the the first of two qualifying races. USA Today Images
